FUNCTIONAL VS OBJECT ORIENTATION

Where is functions?
FUNCTIONAL		OBJECT ORIENTED					JAVA 8
Independent		Bound to object or classes.		Functional interface (Seems independent
				Called as method.				but bound to object or class again)

Value state
FUNCTIONAL		OBJECT ORIENTED					JAVA 8
Immutable		Mutable							Immutable if you desire

Function chaining
FUNCTIONAL		OBJECT ORIENTED					JAVA 8
Yes				Yes if in same instance			Lambda functions may chain

Synchronization and multicore support
FUNCTIONAL		OBJECT ORIENTED					JAVA 8
Great!!!		Exist but really a cumbersome	Some much easy than Java 7.
			